
Tomcat 7 setup in Eclipse

1. Copy K:\Apps Tools\tomcat7\ to C:\Temp\Java\tomcat7

2. In Eclipse Server view, click new and select Apache tomcat 7.
 
 
Eclipse Local Development Setup

1. Add dimension dvlpPC and SharedResources project into workspace

	Select following path from Serana Explorer,  right click "Add to Workspace"
	Dimensions 
       |
       +  dimprd [..] 
             |
	         + Repository Projects
	                   |
	                   +  Eclipse Project Containers
	                                |
	                                + S21NA:NA_ENV [NA_ENV Project]
	                                            |
	                                            + S21NA:NA_ENV [NA_ENV Project]
	                                                       |
	                                                       + dvlpPC [dvlpPC/]
	                                                       + SharedResources [SharedResources/]

2. Setup eclipse User library IBM_WAS_RUNTIME and S21_CSAWDS_EAR_LIBS

    Copy all files ( include sub directory ) from IT server varhdv241 /WebSphere/AppServer/plugins folder to C:\Temp\S21_workspace\WebSphere_AppServer_plugins\ directory;
    Copy all files ( do no include sub directory ) from IT server varhdv241 /WebSphere/AppServer/profiles/AppSrv01/installedApps/varhdv241Cell01/csawds.ear folder to C:\Temp\S21_workspace\csawds_ear_libs\ to directory;

3. import s21extn_eclipse_userlibraries.xml into eclipse User Library.

4. replace TransactionScope.java with TransactionScope.java.txt, modify the jdbc url if needed.

5. replace CanonS21SessionValidate.java with CanonS21SessionValidate.java.txt, modify getFullName method or other method if needed.

6. add CUSTOM_ONLINE_UI and other online project to server.
